  "body": "***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: Text wrapped in tildes displayed with the bold font on iOS instead of italic. \r\nNote: text wrapped in asterisks displays with the bold font as well - issue is that we need an italic for text in tildes.\r\n\r\n**Note**: it's all fine on Android.\r\nOn desktop app there is no font at all applied but text is parsed (i.e. the `~text~` and `*bold*` displayed without asterisks/tildes). Related issue for desktop https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/5275\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nItalic font applied to for text wrapped in tildes on iOS\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nBold font applied to for text wrapped in tildes on iOS\r\n\r\n<img width=\"294\" alt=\"screenshot 2018-11-07 at 15 28 26\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/48134164-cd7e0400-e2a1-11e8-918a-77a7f99638f9.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create new account\r\n- Navigate to any chat (e.g. create unique public chat) \r\n- Send `~I'm italic~` and verify there is italic font applied to the text\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.30 (11730) \r\n* Operating System: iOS (12.0.1)",
